      <div class="modal-body"><h4><b>A Good Way to Invest in Real Estate in Canada - REITs</b></h4><br>
        <b>First, what is REITs? </b>
        <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;Private loans are secured by the borrower's property, and the loan-to-value ratio (LTV) of the project is tightly controlled.</p>
        <p> REITs (real estate investment trust), is a way to issue receipts, pooling of investor funds by the specialized investment institutions for real estate investment, operation and management, and the proportion of comprehensive investment income distributed to investors Trust funds. REITs invests in real estate covering various industries such as shopping centers, office buildings, parking lots, hotels, hospitals, nursing homes and so on. The potential benefits come from rental income and income from real estate price appreciation. Since REITs originated in the United States, since 1960 has been 40 years of history. There are currently more than 190 listed REITs in the United States with total assets of approximately $ 439 billion, which are traded on major exchanges. Canada's first REIT was launched in 1993, 20 years later, to more than 40 REITs, the largest five REITs market value, accounting for half of the Canadian REITs market. RioCan is Canada's largest REIT, with nearly 300 stores in Canada and 31 stores in the United States, with a current yield of 5.6%.</p>
<b>Second, investment What are the advantages of REITs?</b>
        <p>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;
          REITs have the advantages of stable returns, decentralized risk, strong liquidity, tax incentives and other advantages.<br>
          1. Income stability<br>
          REITs' cash flow, mainly from rental income, management and maintenance costs and occupancy rate, the income is relatively stable, Canada REITs usually 75-90% of the current year's dividends distributed to shareholders, so the investment REITs will enjoy stability every year Of the cash income.  
          2. Risk diversification<br>
          REITs are generally initiated and managed by professional real estate companies. They can reasonably select the investment projects and can manage them scientifically, which greatly reduces the investment risk from the operation and management. Second, the size of the Fund is relatively large, which can be widely invested in various types of real estate projects, thus diversifying the investment risk. In addition, REITs and other stock markets, bond assets, the correlation coefficient is low, in the asset allocation by adding REITs, can reduce the risk of the entire portfolio<br>
          3. Mobility, high liquidity<br>
          Direct investment in real estate, a higher amount, but also through intermediaries, procedures cumbersome, and liquidity is not good. REITs are traded on a stock exchange, just like buying and selling stocks. Liquidity, liquidity are better than investment in real estate. In addition, REITs have a low investment threshold and are generally available to investors.。<br>
          4. Tax incentives<br>
          Compared to interest income, REITs have more tax benefits. Investment REITs receive at least half of the cash flow returned on a monthly basis and are not taxable.<br>
          5. Simple and convenient<br>
          REITs investors are owners of many properties but do not have the trouble of ordinary owners: do not worry about vacant properties, do not be afraid to encounter bad tenants, and no tenants will make phone calls, complaints network is not smooth or toilet leaks.
        </p>



